replies.msg:
Marcelo: &ldquo;I&rsquo;ve been linked with several Italian clubs but they were all rumors. The truth is, I love Real Madrid - it&rsquo;s my home and the best club in the world. Madrid has given a lot to football, more than it has received.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Marcelo: &ldquo;The pressure in Madrid is not comparable to anything else in the world of sport. When Madrid does not win, it seems that the world is falling apart. Now we have a good mix of youth and experience. With the right humility we will do well again.&rdquo;

Eden Hazard: &ldquo;Lukaku is a fantastic striker, a bomber who knows how to adapt to all the conditions of the game. He will score a lot - and this is important for a striker - but it would be a mistake to consider him just for that. He can do many things.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Eden Hazard: &ldquo;For example, Lukaku is a specialist for creating what we call 'second plays'. Everyone plays better with him in the team.&quot;

